  "prompt": "Which car services are available in Orlando? How good are they compared to taxis and relative to each other?",
  "response": "In Orlando, several car services are available in addition to traditional taxis. They include rideshare services, private car services, and shuttle services. Below are some options:\n\n1. **Rideshare Services:**\n   - **Uber**: Widely used and offers a range of service levels from budget rides to luxury options.\n   - **Lyft**: Similar to Uber, it provides various ride options and is also popular for its ease of use and reliability.\n\n2. **Private Car Services:**\n   - **Mears Transportation Group**: A reputable local company offering private car services, including luxury vehicles and limousines.\n   - **ExecuCar**: Offers high-end car services with professional drivers for business travel and special occasions.\n\n3. **Shuttle Services:**\n   - **SuperShuttle**: Offers shared ride airport shuttle services, which can be more economical for group travel.\n   - **GO Airport Shuttle**: Another airport shuttle service that provides shared and private rides to and from Orlando International Airport.\n\n**Comparison to Taxis:**\n- **Cost**: Rideshare services like Uber and Lyft usually offer more competitive pricing compared to traditional taxis. Prices can vary based on demand and traffic conditions.\n- **Convenience**: Rideshare services typically provide more convenience due to app-based booking, real-time tracking, and cashless payment options. Taxis can be flagged down on the street or booked through a call but may not offer real-time tracking.\n- **Reliability**: Both rideshare and private car services may offer more reliability with scheduled bookings and professional drivers. Traditional taxis are sometimes perceived as less reliable, especially during peak hours.\n- **Comfort and Service Levels**: Private car services and higher-tier rideshare options (like Uber Black) usually offer a higher level of comfort compared to standard taxis and rideshare services.\n\nRelative to each other:\n- **Uber vs. Lyft**: Both are very similar in terms of pricing and service levels. Personal preference, availability, and occasional promotions might make one more appealing than the other.\n- **Mears Transportation vs. ExecuCar**: Mears is more established locally and might offer more comprehensive services, whereas ExecuCar focuses on premium and business-class rides.\n- **SuperShuttle vs. GO Airport Shuttle**: These services are similar in nature, but prices and customer satisfaction might vary. Checking recent reviews and comparing prices for specific routes can help in making a choice.\n\nOverall, rideshare services tend to be preferred by many for their convenience, ease of use, and competitive pricing compared to traditional taxis. Private car services are ideal for those looking for luxury and reliability. Shuttle services are excellent for group travel and airport transfers.",
